<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - SELF TEST INPUT
        SWITCH AND ENGINE WARNING LIGHT - FAULT DETECTION MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>There are no ECM diagnostics for the STI or Warning light circuits.</para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef12518150">3.157</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            and
            <emph type="bold">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="et1251826">3.31</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the circuit diagram and table for the self test input switch and engine warning light.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef12518150" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg7090" filename="../figeg7/EG7090.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.157 - Injector Drive Circuits Diagram</caption>
        </figure>
        <table id="et1251826">
            <title>Table 3.31 - Self Test Input Switch and Engine Warning Light</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="72p"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="72p"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="324p"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="S1T3"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Test STI switch with ignition key "OFF"</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Across Switch Terminals</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>> 1000 ohms open position</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>&#60; than 1000 ohms replace switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Across Switch Terminals</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms closed position</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>> than 5 ohms replace switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Test at STI switch connection with ignition key "OFF"</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>98 to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>> 1000 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>&#60; than 1000 ohms locate short to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Test at STI switch connections with ignition key "ON"</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>98 to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5 &#177; .5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>&#60; than 4.5 v check connections, if 0 volts, check for open/short to ground in ckt.
                                98
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>98 to 98 - G</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5 &#177; .5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>&#60; than 4.5v check connections, if 0 volts, check for open in ground circuit.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">If warning light DOES NOT turn on when key is turned ON.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>1. Check fuse and bulb condition.</para>
                            <para>2. Disconnect (379) from ECM and install breakout box to harness. Jumper terminal 17
                                to ground and
                            </para>
                            <para>note if light is ON.</para>
                            <para>A. If light is ON, the ECM is defective.</para>
                            <para>B. If light does not turn ON, check circuit for open condition.</para>
                            <para>C. If light goes OFF, ECM is defective.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">If warning light STAYS ON after self test.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>1. Check for active fault conditions (use Prolink or STI flash codes).</para>
                            <para>A. If active fault conditions are present correct faults.</para>
                            <para>B. If no fault conditions are present go to step 2.</para>
                            <para>2. Disconnect (379) from ECM and note if LIGHT remains ON.</para>
                            <para>A. If light remains ON, check for short to ground in circuit.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
